      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEPUNGA SUMMIT (1) goes very well at the course and distance with two wins and a placing from five starts. Missed the frame latest (30.31) when seventh over 515m at Sandown in a Grade 5. Looks suited and should go close. CACO MISSILE (7) comes into this as a quickest on the card winner last time at Ballarat, scoring by 1.3 lengths (31.03). Expected to feature again. IT'S BUBBLE TIME (4) tends to take a while to wind up, missing the placings two back but running on to last time finishing second (30.58) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Expecting another good run. SHE'S SAINTLY (5) can feature with the right run.",
